    <main>
        <h2>Ancient City Bagan</h2>
        
        <h2>Ananda Temple</h2>
        <img src="Bagan1.jpg" alt="Ananda Temple">
        <p>&nbsp&nbspAnanda Temple is one of the most stunning and iconic temples in Bagan. Built in the 11th century, it is known for its impressive architecture and beautiful golden spires. Inside, there are magnificent Buddha statues and intricate carvings, making it a key historical and cultural site.</p>
        
        <h2>Shwezigon Pagoda</h2>
        <img src="Bagan2.jpg" alt="Shwezigon Pagoda">
        <p>&nbsp&nbspShwezigon Pagoda is one of Bagan’s most revered religious monuments. Built by King Anawrahta in the 11th century, this golden stupa is a symbol of Myanmar’s rich Buddhist history. Visitors can admire its grandeur, especially during sunset when the golden stupa shines brightly in the fading light.</p>
        
        <h2>Dhammayangyi Temple</h2>
        <img src="Bagan3.jpg" alt="Dhammayangyi Temple">
        <p>&nbsp&nbspDhammayangyi Temple is the largest temple in Bagan, known for its impressive size and unique architecture. The temple was built in the 12th century, and while the interiors are mostly unadorned, the structure’s vastness and historical significance make it a must-visit site.</p>
        
        <h2>Bagan Archaeological Museum</h2>
        <img src="Bagan4.jpg" alt="Bagan Archaeological Museum">
        <p>&nbsp&nbspThe Bagan Archaeological Museum showcases the region’s rich history and cultural heritage. It houses artifacts, sculptures, and inscriptions from the ancient temples of Bagan. The museum provides visitors with valuable insights into the historical and spiritual significance of the Bagan temples.</p>
        
        <h2>Sunset Views from the Temples</h2>
        <img src="Bagan5.jpg" alt="Bagan Sunset">
        <p>&nbsp&nbspOne of the most breathtaking experiences in Bagan is watching the sunset over the ancient temples. Visitors can climb up some of the temples for a panoramic view of the golden pagodas, the lush plains, and the sun setting behind the horizon, creating an unforgettable memory.</p>
